void countDown(int num)

 {

      if (num == 0) // test

                  System.out.println("Blastoff!");

       else {

                  System.out.println("...");

                    countDown(num-1); // recursive call

             } 

}

/*1. what is the output of this code?
The output here will be
...
...
...
Blastoff!*/

//2. modify it so that it prints only the even numbers. 

void countDownEven(int num) {
    if (num == 0) {
        System.out.println("Blastoff!");
    } else {
        if (num % 2 == 0) {
            System.out.println(num);
        }
        countDownEven(num - 1);
    }
}

/*The output here will be
6
4
2
Blastoff!*/

/*3. what is the time complexity of this algorithm and why?
It would be O(n)because one recursive call per decrement until num == 0.*/
